    <item>
      <title>Research Month Call for Abstracts  at Blackburn Center (Armour J. Blackburn University Center)</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52081220496197/huge/628b5f02849845f7c0bcb4d7231faf09b376217e.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Sun, 01 Mar 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>We are pleased to invite you to participate in Howard University Research Month 2026 by submitting your research abstract for the Annual Research Symposium, the premier showcase of scholarly and creative work across our campus community!</p>

<p> </p>

<p>This year’s Research Symposium will take place April 29 – May 1, 2026, at the Armour J. Blackburn Center, featuring both oral and poster presentations across a wide range of disciplines including Biological &amp; Biomedical Sciences, Physical Sciences &amp; Engineering, Humanities, Social Sciences, Environmental Studies, Business, Creative Arts &amp; Design, Education &amp; Outreach, and Translational &amp; Clinical Sciences.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>All abstracts must be submitted electronically by 11:59 p.m. on Sunday March 1,  2026.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Submitting an abstract is a wonderful opportunity to highlight your research, engage with peers and mentors, and contribute to the vibrant intellectual community at Howard University. Whether you are an undergraduate, graduate student, postdoctoral scholar, faculty member, or staff researcher, we encourage you to share your work and be part of this dynamic celebration of discovery! Howard University Research Month</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Submit your abstract and find more details at: <a href="https://researchmonth.howard.edu/">https://researchmonth.howard.edu/</a></p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/research-month-call-for-abstracts">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Research Month Call for Abstracts &amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Mar 1%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AWe are pleased to invite you to participate in Howard University Research Month 2026 by submitting your research abstract for the Annual Research Symposium%2C the premier showcase of scholarly and creative work across our campus community%21%0A%0A %0A%0AThis year%E2%80%99s Research Symposium will take place April 29 %E2%80%93 May 1%2C 2026%2C at the Armour J. Blackburn Center%2C featuring both oral and poster presentations across a wide range of disciplines including Biological %26 Biomedical Sciences%2C Physical Sciences %26 Engineering%2C Humanities%2C Social Sciences%2C Environmental Studies%2C Business%2C Creative Arts %26 Design%2C Education %26 Outreach%2C and Translational %26 Clinical Sciences.%0A%0A %0A%0AAll abstracts must be submitted electronically by 11%3A59 p.m. on Sunday March 1%2C  2026.%0A%0A %0A%0ASubmitting an abstract is a wonderful opportunity to highlight your research%2C engage with peers and mentors%2C and contribute to the vibrant intellectual community at Howard University. Whether you are an undergraduate%2C graduate student%2C postdoctoral scholar%2C faculty member%2C or staff researcher%2C we encourage you to share your work and be part of this dynamic celebration of discovery%21 Howard University Research Month%0A%0A %0A%0ASubmit your abstract and find more details at%3A https%3A%2F%2Fresearchmonth.howard.edu%2F%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fresearch-month-call-for-abstracts%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
