    <item>
      <title>Transformation to Triumph Black Women's Summit at Childers Hall (Chadwick A. Boseman College of Fine Arts)</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52074120119376/huge/b85c7289227013b3c7565a3f51c94d144d49bb87.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Sun, 01 Mar 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Transformation to Triumph Black Women’s Summit</p>

<p>Evolving. Empowered. Enlightened.
<br /> </p>

<p>The Transformation to Triumph Black Women’s Summit is a three-day experience designed to uplift, equip, and restore Black women navigating layoffs, furloughs, and major life transitions. Taking place February 27 (virtual) and February 28–March 1 (in person at Howard University), this dynamic summit creates space for healing, strategy, and renewed purpose.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>The summit will bring together thought leaders, practitioners, and change-makers committed to supporting Black women as they reclaim their power and chart their next chapter.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Participants will engage in interactive workshops, inspiring speakers, and practical tools centered on:</p>

<p>Personal finance and investment</p>

<p>Health and wellbeing</p>

<p>Career advancement and entrepreneurship</p>

<p>Purpose, identity, and life path</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Whether you are rebuilding, reimagining, or redefining your future, Transformation to Triumph offers community, clarity, and concrete strategies to move forward with confidence and intention. This is more than a summit—it’s a turning point.</p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/transformation-to-triumph-black-womens-summit">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Transformation to Triumph Black Women%27s Summit&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Mar 1%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0ATransformation to Triumph Black Women%E2%80%99s Summit%0A%0AEvolving. Empowered. Enlightened.%0A %0A%0AThe Transformation to Triumph Black Women%E2%80%99s Summit is a three-day experience designed to uplift%2C equip%2C and restore Black women navigating layoffs%2C furloughs%2C and major life transitions. Taking place February 27 %28virtual%29 and February 28%E2%80%93March 1 %28in person at Howard University%29%2C this dynamic summit creates space for healing%2C strategy%2C and renewed purpose.%0A%0A %0A%0AThe summit will bring together thought leaders%2C practitioners%2C and change-makers committed to supporting Black women as they reclaim their power and chart their next chapter.%0A%0A %0A%0AParticipants will engage in interactive workshops%2C inspiring speakers%2C and practical tools centered on%3A%0A%0APersonal finance and investment%0A%0AHealth and wellbeing%0A%0ACareer advancement and entrepreneurship%0A%0APurpose%2C identity%2C and life path%0A%0A %0A%0AWhether you are rebuilding%2C reimagining%2C or redefining your future%2C Transformation to Triumph offers community%2C clarity%2C and concrete strategies to move forward with confidence and intention. This is more than a summit%E2%80%94it%E2%80%99s a turning point.%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Ftransformation-to-triumph-black-womens-summit%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
